<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:30PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Bibb,
southeastern Monroe and southwestern Jones Counties through 100 PM
EDT...
At 1230 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Lake Tobesofkee, or 10
miles south of Forsyth, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Macon, Wesleyan, Lake Tobesofkee, Bolingbroke, Arkwright, Dames
Ferry, Plant Scherer and Jarrell Plantation.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
